import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['x'] = pd.to_datetime(data['x'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='x', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['x'].min(), color='red', label=f"Min: {data['x'].min().strftime('%Y-%m-%d')}")
    plt.axvline(data['x'].max(), color='green', label=f"Max: {data['x'].max().strftime('%Y-%m-%d')}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of x-coordinates?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['y'] = pd.to_numeric(data['y'])
    sns.boxplot(x=data['y'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of y-coordinates?', wrap=True)
    plt.axvline(x=data['y'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['y'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = np.sqrt(data['x']**2 + data['y']**2)
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='distance', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(x=data['distance'].mean(), color='red', label=f"Mean: {data['distance'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average distance of the points from the origin?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
